(9, 3, 'Toss your Halloween candy, Hershey\'s has launched Hot Cocoa Kisses', 'Hershey’s has launched Hot Cocoa Kisses, the candy’s first new holiday flavor in nearly a decade. ', '<div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-article-body\" data-pb-name=\"Article Body (Elements)\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"fxbPiu1dbbEd7r\"> <div class=\"\"> </div> <div class=\"collection collection-cards\"> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p data-page=\"1\">There’s no point in hanging on to that leftover Halloween candy. This season’s tastiest treat is a new arrival.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>Perfectly timed to cooler weather coming, Hershey’s has just launched Hot Cocoa Kisses, the candy’s first new holiday flavor in nearly a decade.</p> </div></div> <div class=\"mobile-dfp inline-ad hidden-desktop\" data-inline-ad-count=\"1\"> <div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-dfp\" data-pb-name=\"DFP Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"f0WjqBiUDp6j8r\"> <div class=\"pb-ad pb-ad-prod ad-300x250 hidden-desktop relative\"> <div class=\"ad-caption-text align-center uppercase\">Advertisement</div> <div id=\"lifestyle_eats_1475\" class=\"hidden\"> </div> </div> <script>(function(){function loadAd(){window.serviceCallbacks.push(function(){if(window.services.dfpService&&window.googletag&&googletag.pubadsReady)window.services.dfpService.appendAd({id:\"lifestyle_eats_1475\",adType:\"cube\",slotName:\"/4011/trb.nydn/lifestyle/eats\",displayMobile:true,displayDesktop:false,isOOP:false,is5x1:false,dimensionsString:\"[[300, 250]]\",sizemapString:\"\",sizemapRefresh:\"false\",refreshOnPhotoChange:false,includeInA9:true,includeInIndexExchange:false,options:{ptype:\"s\",iab:\"biz\",apv:\"false\",\r\nsite:\"trb.nydn\",slug:\"ny-fea-hersheys-hot-cocoa-kisses-launch-20181102\",cid:\"109559751\",at:\"Halloween,TheHersheyCo.\",kw:\"bag,candy,treat,crme,chocolate,Cane,Hershey,marshmallow,flavor,goody,kiss,arrival,cup,cube,winter,weather,supplies,season,halloweencandy,Halloweencandy,tastiesttreat,point,Halloween,nothing,Kisses\",tg:\"\",design:\"arc\",nopulse:true}},false,true);else setTimeout(loadAd,500)})}loadAd()})();</script> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>There’s nothing more soothing than a cup of hot chocolate on a cold winter’s day and now all that flavor is packed into a tiny bite-sized sweet.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>The new goodies look just like traditional milk chocolate kisses on the outside, but they’re crammed with marshmallow flavored crème to mimic the fluffy white cubes that often dot cocoa cups.</p> </div></div> <div class=\"desktop-nativo mobile-yieldmo inline-ad \" data-inline-ad-count=\"2\"> <span class=\"hidden-desktop\"> <div class=\"wrapper clearfix col pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-yieldmo\" data-pb-name=\"Yieldmo Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"\"> <div id=\"ym_2001405\"></div> <script>window.serviceCallbacks.push(function(){if(window.isMobile.any()&&window.services.isAdEnabled(\"yieldmo\")){var el=document.getElementById(\"ym_2001405\");if(false)window.services.lazyLoadService.addPendingObject({id:\"ym_2001405\",el:el,load:function(){window.services.YieldmoService.load({id:\"ym_2001405\",el:el})}});else window.services.YieldmoService.load({id:\"ym_2001405\",el:el})}});</script> </div></span> <span class=\"hidden-mobile\"><div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-nativo\" data-pb-name=\"Nativo Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"fXle2Q15Ep6j8r\"> </div></span> </div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>They’re available in 8-ounce bags for about $3.50 and 10-ounce bags for around $4 and will be sold while supplies last or till the end of the holiday season.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>Other seasonal Kisses have included Pumpkin Spice and Candy Cane.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item card-border-bottom card-border-bottom-thick card-border-bottom-dark\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p></p> <div class=\"spaced spaced-md spaced-bottom hidden-mobile\"></div> <div class=\"spaced spaced-sm spaced-bottom hidden-desktop hidden-tablet\"></div> </div></div> <ul class=\"trb_ar_rt\" data-c-typename=\"article\"> <li class=\"trb_ar_rt_li\"> <a class=\"trb_ar_rt_a\" title=\"Halloween\" href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/tags/halloween/\">Halloween</a> </li> <li class=\"trb_ar_rt_li\"> <a class=\"trb_ar_rt_a\" title=\"The Hershey Co.\" href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/tags/the-hershey-co/\">The Hershey Co.</a> </li> </ul> </div> </div>', 'https://www.nydailynews.com/resizer/mu7f-SGTHQKfXekmVsfhRUhz6gI=/1400x0/www.trbimg.com/img-5bdcc12a/turbine/ny-1541194021-4fj9iblv4a-snap-image', '2018-11-03', 'Gina Salamone', 'Halloween, candy'),
(10, 5, 'What \'Bohemian Rhapsody\' gets right — and wrong — about Queen and Freddie Mercury', 'Some of details included in the new Queen biopic about the band’s illustrious heyday strike exactly the right note, while a few others seem to have gotten the Hollywood treatment.', '<div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-article-body\" data-pb-name=\"Article Body (Elements)\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"fxbPiu1dbbEd7r\"> <div class=\"\"> </div> <div class=\"collection collection-cards\"> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p data-page=\"1\"></p><p data-page=\"1\"><strong><em>Warning: This article contains “Bohemian Rhapsody” spoilers.</em></strong></p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>Some of details included in the new Queen biopic about the band’s illustrious heyday strike exactly the right note, while a few others seem to have gotten the Hollywood treatment.</p> </div></div> <div class=\"mobile-dfp inline-ad hidden-desktop\" data-inline-ad-count=\"1\"> <div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-dfp\" data-pb-name=\"DFP Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"fgiDix1ucq7j8r\"> <div class=\"pb-ad pb-ad-prod ad-300x250 hidden-desktop relative\"> <div class=\"ad-caption-text align-center uppercase\">Advertisement</div> <div id=\"entertainment_movies_1335\" class=\"hidden\"> </div> </div> <script>(function(){function loadAd(){window.serviceCallbacks.push(function(){if(window.services.dfpService&&window.googletag&&googletag.pubadsReady)window.services.dfpService.appendAd({id:\"entertainment_movies_1335\",adType:\"cube\",slotName:\"/4011/trb.nydn/entertainment/movies\",displayMobile:true,displayDesktop:false,isOOP:false,is5x1:false,dimensionsString:\"[[300, 250]]\",sizemapString:\"\",sizemapRefresh:\"false\",refreshOnPhotoChange:false,includeInA9:true,includeInIndexExchange:false,options:{ptype:\"s\",iab:\"ent\",\r\napv:\"false\",site:\"trb.nydn\",slug:\"ny-ent-bohemian-rhapsody-fact-fiction-20181101\",cid:\"109546062\",at:\"FreddieMercury,EMIGroupLtd.\",kw:\"Mercury,rhapsody,movie,band,Austin,mercury,Smile,fiction,Taylor,staffell,song,Freddie,Queen,tooth,performance,guitarist,Staffell,spoiler,audience,Foster,singer,actor,Mary,taylor,austin\",tg:\"PopCulture,Celebrity,Music\",design:\"arc\",nopulse:true}},false,true);else setTimeout(loadAd,500)})}loadAd()})();</script> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>Here’s a look at a few moments in “Bohemian Rhapsody” that are historically accurate, as well as some parts in the movie that are matters of fiction.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p><strong>Fact: </strong><strong>Queen’s performance at Live Aid </strong></p> </div></div> <div class=\"desktop-nativo mobile-yieldmo inline-ad \" data-inline-ad-count=\"2\"> <span class=\"hidden-desktop\"> <div class=\"wrapper clearfix col pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-yieldmo\" data-pb-name=\"Yieldmo Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"\"> <div id=\"ym_2001400\"></div> <script>window.serviceCallbacks.push(function(){if(window.isMobile.any()&&window.services.isAdEnabled(\"yieldmo\")){var el=document.getElementById(\"ym_2001400\");if(false)window.services.lazyLoadService.addPendingObject({id:\"ym_2001400\",el:el,load:function(){window.services.YieldmoService.load({id:\"ym_2001400\",el:el})}});else window.services.YieldmoService.load({id:\"ym_2001400\",el:el})}});</script> </div></span> <span class=\"hidden-mobile\"><div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-nativo\" data-pb-name=\"Nativo Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"f0k7FF1Ocq7j8r\"> <div class=\"hidden-mobile\"> <div id=\"896\" data-nativo-id-desktop=\"1089976\" class=\"desktop-nativo-ad trb_ar_nt\"></div> </div> </div></span> </div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>The band’s show-stealing 25-minute set at the star-studded Live Aid concert in 1985 is widely regarded as not just one of the best Queen performances ever, but as one of the greatest rock shows of all-time.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>The movie captures the energy and magic of that performance with an impressive attention to detail. The actors made it a point to duplicate even the subtlest onstage movements that their characters made in real life to make it as close to a mirror image as possible.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>“We had to be very, very particular,” Joseph Mazzello, who plays bassist John Deacon, told the Daily News. “Every movement had to be replicated from the actual performance because it was so famous. We wanted people to go look at that, and look at what we were doing, and then go watch the movie and be like, ‘See, we put in the effort.’”</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>Although the final cut of the movie only shows four of the seven songs Queen played that evening at Wembley Stadium, the actors filmed the full set, and it’s expected to appear in its entirety on the DVD release of “Bohemian Rhapsody.”</p> </div></div> <div class=\"mobile-nativo inline-ad hidden-desktop\" data-inline-ad-count=\"3\"> <div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-nativo\" data-pb-name=\"Nativo Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"f0uPH7PZcq7j8r\"> <div class=\"hidden-desktop\"> <div id=\"19981\" data-nativo-id-mobile=\"1089976\" class=\"mobile-nativo-ad trb_ar_nt\"></div> </div> </div></div> <div data-type=\"oembed_response\" class=\"card card-pull-center collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <div class=\"element element-oembed oembed-youtube responsive-embed-16x9 relative\"> <iframe width=\"480\" height=\"270\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/A22oy8dFjqc?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"\" id=\"1541217965536_TBOtherPlayer_10\"></iframe></div> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p><strong>Fiction: How Freddie Mercury met the band and Mary Austin</strong></p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>The movie suggests that Mercury — whose real name was Farrokh Bulsara — met Brian May and Roger Taylor on the night that Tim Staffell, the lead singer of their previous band Smile, bailed on the group. The scene shows Mercury introducing himself, wowing them with his singing voice and joining the band from there.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>In reality, Mercury was already friends with Staffell and met May and Taylor through him before Smile ever dissipated. Staffell leaving Smile did open the door for Mercury to join musical forces with May and Taylor.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>The film also makes it look like Mercury met Mary Austin, whom he dated and ultimately remained lifelong friends with, on that same night. But Austin actually dated May before Mercury — and the singer asked the guitarist if it would be OK if he dated Austin.</p> </div></div> <div class=\"mobile-yieldmo inline-ad hidden-desktop\" data-inline-ad-count=\"4\"> <div class=\"wrapper clearfix col pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-yieldmo\" data-pb-name=\"Yieldmo Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"\"> <div id=\"ym_1610965632225229372\"></div> <script>window.serviceCallbacks.push(function(){if(window.isMobile.any()&&window.services.isAdEnabled(\"yieldmo\")){var el=document.getElementById(\"ym_1610965632225229372\");if(true)window.services.lazyLoadService.addPendingObject({id:\"ym_1610965632225229372\",el:el,load:function(){window.services.YieldmoService.load({id:\"ym_1610965632225229372\",el:el})}});else window.services.YieldmoService.load({id:\"ym_1610965632225229372\",el:el})}});</script> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>“Freddie came up to me one day and said, ‘Are you serious with Mary? Can I ask her out?’ And he did, and they were lovers for a long time,” May told <a href=\"https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/brian-may-discusses-unusual-beautiful-love-story-freddie-mercury-biopic-053041969.html\" target=\"_blank\">Yahoo Music</a>.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p><strong>FACT: The making of ‘We Will Rock You’</strong></p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>The rousing stadium classic is one of the most universally known and interactive songs in the rock genre, and that’s exactly how May intended for it to be when he wrote it.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>“Bohemian Rhapsody” shows May sharing the idea for a song that allows the audience to essentially supply the beat, coming up with “We Will Rock You.”</p> </div></div> <div class=\"mobile-dfp inline-ad hidden-desktop\" data-inline-ad-count=\"5\"> <div class=\"wrapper clearfix full pb-feature pb-layout-item pb-f-ads-dfp\" data-pb-name=\"DFP Ad\" data-pb-curated=\"curated\" id=\"f0cwnpqbdq7j8r\"> <div class=\"pb-ad pb-ad-prod ad-300x250 hidden-desktop relative\"> <div class=\"ad-caption-text align-center uppercase\">Advertisement</div> <div id=\"entertainment_movies_1721\" class=\"hidden\"> </div> </div> <script>(function(){function loadAd(){window.serviceCallbacks.push(function(){if(window.services.dfpService&&window.googletag&&googletag.pubadsReady)window.services.dfpService.appendAd({id:\"entertainment_movies_1721\",adType:\"cube\",slotName:\"/4011/trb.nydn/entertainment/movies\",displayMobile:true,displayDesktop:false,isOOP:false,is5x1:false,dimensionsString:\"[[300, 250]]\",sizemapString:\"\",sizemapRefresh:\"false\",refreshOnPhotoChange:false,includeInA9:true,includeInIndexExchange:false,options:{ptype:\"s\",iab:\"ent\",\r\napv:\"false\",site:\"trb.nydn\",slug:\"ny-ent-bohemian-rhapsody-fact-fiction-20181101\",cid:\"109546062\",at:\"FreddieMercury,EMIGroupLtd.\",kw:\"Mercury,rhapsody,movie,band,Austin,mercury,Smile,fiction,Taylor,staffell,song,Freddie,Queen,tooth,performance,guitarist,Staffell,spoiler,audience,Foster,singer,actor,Mary,taylor,austin\",tg:\"PopCulture,Celebrity,Music\",design:\"arc\",nopulse:true}},false,true);else setTimeout(loadAd,500)})}loadAd()})();</script> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>The guitarist has confirmed that’s the real story for the 1977 hit in a number of interviews over the years, referencing an experience he had where the audience sang along to every song.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>“A light went off and I thought, ‘We shouldn\'t fight this, we should embrace it!’ People didn\'t do that at the time at rock concerts,” May told <a href=\"https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/rock/7972856/queen-we-will-rock-you-we-are-the-champions-jock-jam-interview\" target=\"_blank\">Billboard</a> last year. “I thought, ‘How interesting — if I wrote something, the audience could participate it to the point that they could lead the band?’ I went to sleep and woke up with ‘We Will Rock You’ in my head. When you\'re at a show you can hardly move, but you can stomp your feet and chant and clap and lead us.”</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"oembed_response\" class=\"card card-pull-center collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <div class=\"element element-oembed oembed-youtube responsive-embed-16x9 relative\"> <iframe width=\"480\" height=\"270\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/7954xNZcRUI?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen=\"\" id=\"1541217965543_TBOtherPlayer_20\"></iframe></div> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p><strong>FICTION: Mercury’s HIV diagnosis</strong></p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>In the movie, Mercury learns he has the disease shortly before his band’s 1985 performance at Live Aid and informs his bandmates of his diagnosis during rehearsals the week of the show.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>In reality, however, Mercury is believed to have been diagnosed with the disease no earlier than 1986, meaning the timeline was off.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>He died from complications stemming from AIDS in 1991, when he was 45.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p><strong>FACT: Freddie’s teeth </strong></p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>During an early portion of “Bohemian Rhapsody,” Mercury credits having four extra incisors in his mouth for giving him a wider singing range.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>It has indeed been widely reported that Mercury had four extra teeth, and that he never got his overbite fixed because he was afraid it would impact his voice.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>Actor Rami Malek, who plays Mercury in the film, wore fake teeth throughout the movie to better capture the rock icon’s appearance.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p><strong>FICTION: Record exec Ray Foster</strong></p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>Mike Myers — better known for comedies such as “Austin Powers” and “Shrek” — makes a cameo in the movie as a close-minded EMI record executive named Ray Foster who refuses to release the song “Bohemian Rhapsody” as a single, pushing for “You’re My Best Friend” instead.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"text\" class=\"card collection-item\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <p>It appears, however, that Foster was not a real person, but rather a composite character constructed for the movie.</p> </div></div> <div data-type=\"image\" class=\"card card-pull-center card-captioned collection-item card-border-bottom card-border-bottom-thick card-border-bottom-dark\"> <div class=\" card-content \"> <figure class=\"\"> <div class=\"full-width img-container \"> <img class=\"b-lazy full-width\" alt=\"Mike Myers plays a character named Ray Foster in &quot;Bohemian Rhapsody.&quot;\" data-src=\"https://www.nydailynews.com/resizer/9oNbqH0FjbtrHADrNga9Rn6S2FY=/1400x0/www.trbimg.com/img-5bdb4582/turbine/ny-1541096830-i5npbto94j-snap-image\" src=\"/pb/resources/images/tinygif.gif\"> </div> <figcaption class=\"caption-text spaced spaced-top spaced-sm flex-container-row justify-space-between \"> <div>Mike Myers plays a character named Ray Foster in \"Bohemian Rhapsody.\" (20th Century Fox)</div> </figcaption> </figure> </div></div> <ul class=\"trb_ar_rt\" data-c-typename=\"article\"> <li class=\"trb_ar_rt_li\"> <a class=\"trb_ar_rt_a\" title=\" Freddie Mercury\" href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/tags/freddie-mercury/\"> Freddie Mercury</a> </li> <li class=\"trb_ar_rt_li\"> <a class=\"trb_ar_rt_a\" title=\"EMI Group Ltd.\" href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/tags/emi-group-ltd/\">EMI Group Ltd.</a> </li> </ul> </div> </div>', 'https://www.nydailynews.com/resizer/9oNbqH0FjbtrHADrNga9Rn6S2FY=/1400x0/www.trbimg.com/img-5bdb4582/turbine/ny-1541096830-i5npbto94j-snap-image', '2018-11-03', 'Peter Sblendorio', 'Suzuki, Swift');
